g & =\left\{ \left(1,4\right),\left(a,0\right),\left(-2,-1\right),\left(3,-3\right),\left(2,a\right)\right\} 
\end{align*}

\end_inset

Calcule el dominio y rango de 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

 y 
\begin_inset Formula $g.$
\end_inset

 Obtenga además 
\begin_inset Formula $f+g,fg,f/g,g/f,g\circ f,f\circ g$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset VSpace defskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Solution
En virtud a la definición de 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

 y 
\begin_inset Formula $g$
\end_inset

 se tiene que 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{array}{lll}
\operatorname*{Dom}\left(f\right)=\left\{ 1,a,-1,2\right\}  &  & \operatorname*{Ran}\left(f\right)=\left\{ 2,3,-2\right\} \\
\operatorname*{Dom}\left(g\right)=\left\{ 1,a,-2,3,2\right\}  &  & \operatorname*{Ran}\left(g\right)=\left\{ 4,0,-1,-3,a\right\} .
\end{array}
\]

\end_inset

En 
\begin_inset Formula $\operatorname*{Dom}\left(f\right)\cap\operatorname*{Dom}\left(g\right)=\left\{ 1,a,2\right\} $
\end_inset

 se definen las funciones
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
f+g & =\left\{ \left(1,6\right),\left(a,3\right),\left(2,a-2\right)\right\} \\
fg & =\left\{ \left(1,8\right),\left(a,0\right),\left(2,-2a\right)\right\} 
\end{align*}

